@@ -0,0 +1,175 @@
+# Audiobookshelf — Keycloak OIDC Integration (GH-60)
+
+This document is the authoritative OIDC specification for the production
+Audiobookshelf instance. It implements GitHub issue
+`yeraziael/slartis-backlog#60`. All runtime objects are provisioned by the
+versioned scripts under `pi/audiobookshelf/scripts/`.
+
+## 1. Architecture
+
+```
+ Operator / User
+      │ HTTPS (audiobookshelf.hl.maier.wtf)
+      ▼
+ ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────┐
+ │  frontproxy  │     │            Audiobookshelf (RP)                │
+ │ nginx-proxy  │────▶│  - local break-glass account `admin`         │
+ │   :443       │     │  - OIDC client (confidential)                │
+ └──────────────┘     │  - users bound by OIDC `sub`                 │
+                     │  - guest = read-only, admin = server admin   │
+                     └──────────────────────────────────────────────┘
+                              │ Authorization Code Flow (HTTPS)
+                              ▼
+                     ┌────────────────────────────────┐
+                     │  Keycloak  (IdP, realm `homelab`)│
+                     │  auth.hl.maier.wtf              │
+                     │  groups: audiobookshelf-users   │
+                     │          audiobookshelf-admins  │
+                     └────────────────────────────────┘
+```
+
+### Trust boundaries
+- **External**: browser ↔ frontproxy ↔ Audiobookshelf, all HTTPS.
+- **Internal**: Audiobookshelf ↔ Keycloak over the docker network
+  (`frontproxy` / internal). Keycloak issuer URL is the external HTTPS
+  endpoint; internal container names are never used as issuer/redirect.
+- **Local-only**: the `admin` break-glass account authenticates locally and
+  never touches Keycloak. It is the recovery path when Keycloak is unavailable.
+
+### Authentication flow (Authorization Code, confidential)
+1. User clicks **Keycloak** on the ABS login page.
+2. ABS redirects to Keycloak `authorization_endpoint` with
+   `response_type=code`, `client_id=audiobookshelf`, `scope=openid profile email`,
+   `redirect_uri=https://audiobookshelf.hl.maier.wtf/auth/openid/callback`.
+3. Keycloak authenticates and returns an authorization code.
+4. ABS exchanges the code (with `client_secret`, server-side) at the token
+   endpoint, receives `id_token` + `access_token`.
+5. ABS fetches `userinfo` (contains `sub`, `preferred_username`, `email`,
+   `groups`, `abs_role`).
+6. ABS matches the user by `sub`; auto-registers on first login; applies group
+   → role mapping; issues a local session.
+
+### Identity binding (stable, by `sub`)
+Audiobookshelf 2.35.1 binds the local account **exclusively by the OIDC
+`sub` claim** (`User.findUserFromOpenIdUserInfo` → `getUserByOpenIDSub`).
+The `sub` is persisted on the user (`extraData.authOpenIDSub`). A change of
+`preferred_username` is attributed to the same account (no duplicate is
+created). `authOpenIDMatchExistingBy` is left **null** so existing local
+accounts are never auto-linked by mutable email/username (GH-60 §4.2).
+
+### Rights flow
+`groups` (real Keycloak groups) → `abs_role` (derived client roles)
+→ ABS user type:
+
+| Keycloak group(s)                | client role | ABS type | effective rights |
+|----------------------------------|-------------|----------|------------------|
+| `audiobookshelf-users`           | `guest`     | `guest`  | read-only (play/download/access, no upload/edit/delete/mgmt) |
+| `audiobookshelf-admins` (+users) | `admin`     | `admin`  | full server administration |
+
+`abs_role` is emitted by the **audiobookshelf-roles** protocol mapper
+(Role Membership) from the group→client-role mappings. The raw `groups`
+claim is also emitted (audit/transparency).
+
+## 2. OIDC configuration
+
+| Property | Value |
+|---|---|
+| Identity Provider | existing Keycloak, realm `homelab` |
+| Issuer | `https://auth.hl.maier.wtf/realms/homelab` |
+| Discovery | `https://auth.hl.maier.wtf/realms/homelab/.well-known/openid-configuration` |
+| Client ID | `audiobookshelf` |
+| Client type | confidential (client secret, server-side) |
+| Flow | Authorization Code |
+| Direct Access Grants | disabled |
+| Implicit Flow | disabled |
+| Service Accounts | disabled |
+| PKCE (S256) | **not configurable in 2.35.1 — see §4** |
+| Scopes | `openid profile email` |
+| Redirect URI | `https://audiobookshelf.hl.maier.wtf/auth/openid/callback` |
+| Post-Logout Redirect | `https://audiobookshelf.hl.maier.wtf/login` |
+| Web Origin | `https://audiobookshelf.hl.maier.wtf` |
+| End-session endpoint | `https://auth.hl.maier.wtf/realms/homelab/protocol/openid-connect/logout` |
+| Auto-provisioning | enabled (`authOpenIDAutoRegister=true`) |
+| Auto-launch OIDC | disabled (`authOpenIDAutoLaunch=false`) — local login retained |
+| Group claim consumed by ABS | `abs_role` |
+| Token signing | `RS256` (validated via JWKS, expiry, issuer, audience, state, nonce) |
+
+### Claims
+| Claim | Purpose | Presence |
+|---|---|---|
+| `sub` | stable identity key (persisted, used for binding) | required |
+| `preferred_username` | visible ABS username | required |
+| `email` | user info | if present in Keycloak |
+| `groups` | real Keycloak group membership (audit) | required (non-empty) |
+| `abs_role` | derived role tokens `admin`/`guest` (admission + role mapping) | required (non-empty) |
+
+### Keycloak groups & roles
+- Realm groups: `audiobookshelf-users`, `audiobookshelf-admins`
+  (the latter is a **child** of the former).
+- Client roles of `audiobookshelf`: `admin`, `guest`.
+- Group → client-role mapping:
+  - `audiobookshelf-users` → `guest`
+  - `audiobookshelf-admins` → `admin`
+- **Invariant (documented combined condition, GH-60 §5.2):** every member of
+  `audiobookshelf-admins` is also a member of `audiobookshelf-users`. The
+  provisioning script and the group-maintenance runbook enforce this; an admin
+  therefore always satisfies the login-admission group.
+- Seed: `michael` is a member of **both** groups (the only initial admin).
+
+## 3. Logout (RP-Initiated)
+ABS 2.35.1 supports RP-Initiated Logout natively
+(`OidcAuthStrategy.getEndSessionUrl`): on logout it terminates the local
+session and redirects to Keycloak `end_session_endpoint` with
+`id_token_hint` (the `id_token` saved at login) and
+`post_logout_redirect_uri=https://audiobookshelf.hl.maier.wtf/login`.
+This ends the Keycloak SSO session, enabling a different user to log in
+afterwards. The local **Keycloak** button remains available.
+
+## 4. Known technical limitations (with evidence)
+
+### PKCE (S256) — NOT supported for the web/confidential flow
+- **Version:** Audiobookshelf `2.35.1` (image digest
+  `sha256:1eef6716183c52abafe5405e7d6be8390248ecd59c7488c44af871757ac8fc4d`).
+- **Evidence:** the server-settings model exposes no PKCE toggle
+  (`/app/server/objects/settings/ServerSettings.js` enumerates only
+  `authOpenID*` fields; there is **no** `authOpenIDUsePkce`). PKCE is generated
+  only for the separate mobile flow (`generatePkce` in `OidcAuthStrategy.js`).
+- **Impact:** the Authorization Code flow for the web client is not protected
+  by PKCE. The client is **confidential** (secret exchanged server-side), which
+  mitigates code-interception for this first-party deployment.
+- **Blocker?** **No.** GH-60 §3.1 explicitly states missing native PKCE support
+  is **not** a blocker, only requiring documentation (provided here).
+- **Smallest upstream change:** add an `authOpenIDUsePkce` flag to
+  `ServerSettings` and pass `code_challenge`/`code_challenge_method=S256` into
+  the passport `openid-client` strategy `params` for the web flow.
+
+### `preferred_username` is not auto-synced on rename
+- **Evidence:** `verifyCallback` updates the user **type** from the group
+  claim but does not rewrite `username` on subsequent logins; the username is
+  fixed at first auto-registration from `preferred_username`.
+- **Impact:** a rename in Keycloak is correctly attributed to the same local
+  account (no duplicate — the §4.1 hard requirement), but the **displayed**
+  ABS username is not automatically updated. An administrator may rename the
+  local account in the ABS UI if desired.
+- **Blocker?** **No.** The binding-by-`sub` requirement is fully met.
+
+### No native group-name → ABS-role mapping
+- **Evidence:** `OidcAuthStrategy.setUserGroup` only understands the literal
+  role tokens `admin`/`user`/`guest`, not `audiobookshelf-users` /
+  `audiobookshelf-admins`.
+- **Resolution (GH-60 §5.3 permitted integration logic):** a Keycloak
+  Role-Membership mapper (`audiobookshelf-roles`) derives `admin`/`guest`
+  tokens from the authoritative groups into the `abs_role` claim. No second
+  manually maintained role source is introduced — the client roles are derived
+  from the two Keycloak groups.
+
+## 5. Security posture
+- Secrets are provided only via the runtime secret store; never committed,
+  logged, or placed in examples (only `${OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET}` placeholders).
+- Token validation is performed by the `openid-client` library: issuer,
+  signature (JWKS), `exp`, `nbf`, `iat`, audience, `state`, `nonce`, and
+  single-use authorization code. TLS is validated normally. No validation is
+  disabled.
+- Redirect URIs and post-logout URIs are exact HTTPS HTTPS values (no
+  wildcards). Web Origin is the exact external origin (no `*`).
+- Local login is retained only for the `admin` break-glass account.
