@@ -0,0 +1,107 @@
+# Audiobookshelf — Operations & Disaster Recovery Runbook (GH-60)
+
+Covers deployment of the OIDC integration, runtime-secret handling, day-to-day
+operations, break-glass use, and recovery. Implements the documentation areas
+required by GH-60 §11 (deployment, runtime-secrets, operations, DR, break-glass).
+
+## 1. Deployment / configuration parameters
+
+The OIDC settings live in the Audiobookshelf **server settings** (database),
+not in the compose file. They are applied via
+`pi/audiobookshelf/scripts/apply-abs-settings.sh` which `PATCH`es
+`/api/settings`. The canonical values are in
+`pi/audiobookshelf/oidc/abs-server-settings.json` (secret placeholder only).
+
+| Parameter | Value |
+|---|---|
+| `authOpenIDIssuerURL` | `https://auth.hl.maier.wtf/realms/homelab` |
+| `authOpenIDClientID` | `audiobookshelf` |
+| `authOpenIDClientSecret` | runtime secret (Keycloak client secret) |
+| `authOpenIDGroupClaim` | `abs_role` |
+| `authOpenIDAutoRegister` | `true` |
+| `authOpenIDMatchExistingBy` | `null` (never set to email/username) |
+| `authOpenIDAutoLaunch` | `false` (local break-glass login retained) |
+| `authOpenIDSubfolderForRedirectURLs` | `https://audiobookshelf.hl.maier.wtf` |
+
+Start order: Keycloak → frontproxy → audiobookshelf. The OIDC client must
+exist in Keycloak **before** ABS settings are applied. Health check: ABS
+container `healthy` and `GET /` returns the login page; after OIDC, the
+**Keycloak** button appears.
+
+## 2. Runtime secrets
+
+| Secret | Origin | Storage | Rotation |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| OIDC client secret | generated by `setup-keycloak.sh` | runtime secret store consumed by `apply-abs-settings.sh` (`OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET` / `OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET_FILE`) | `rotate-keycloak-secret.sh` |
+| Break-glass `admin` password | generated by `break-glass-setup.sh` | offline, operator-only (Telegram delivery, never persisted by automation) | `break-glass-setup.sh` (re-run) |
+
+Rules:
+- Secrets are never committed, printed, or logged. Scripts refuse to run under
+  `set -x`. The client secret is emitted once to stdout for the operator to
+  capture into the secret store.
+- File-based secrets use restrictive permissions (e.g. `chmod 600`) if a file
+  backend is used.
+
+## 3. Operations
+
+### User onboarding
+1. Create the user in Keycloak realm `homelab`.
+2. Add them to `audiobookshelf-users` (read-only). For admins, add to **both**
+   `audiobookshelf-users` and `audiobookshelf-admins`.
+3. The next login auto-provisions the ABS account (bound by `sub`).
+4. Share the relevant libraries with the user/group in the ABS UI (new accounts
+   have `accessAllLibraries:true` by default; restrict as needed).
+
+### Group maintenance
+- Adding/removing a user from `audiobookshelf-admins` takes effect at the next
+  login (ABS re-evaluates `abs_role` every login; admin revocation downgrades
+  the local account to `guest`, removal of `audiobookshelf-users` denies login).
+- Never create a second, manually maintained role source; the two Keycloak
+  groups are authoritative.
+
+### Permission / rename change
+- Rename in Keycloak: attributed to the same local account (bound by `sub`),
+  display name may be updated manually in ABS if desired.
+- Permission change: change Keycloak group membership; next login applies it.
+
+### Login / logout diagnosis
+- **No Keycloak button:** ABS settings not applied or client missing — re-run
+  `apply-abs-settings.sh`; check ABS logs for `OpenID Connect settings are not valid`.
+- **Login denied:** user not in `audiobookshelf-users` (no `abs_role`); check
+  the `groups`/`abs_role` claims in the ABS OIDC callback debug log
+  (`[OidcAuth]`).
+- **Logout does not end SSO:** verify `authOpenIDLogoutURL` equals the Keycloak
+  `end_session_endpoint` and the post-logout URI is whitelisted.
+
+### Regular secret rotation
+Run `pi/audiobookshelf/scripts/rotate-keycloak-secret.sh`, then re-apply ABS
+settings with the new secret and **restart the audiobookshelf container**
+(ABS caches the OIDC client). Verify old secret fails, new secret works.
+
+## 4. Disaster recovery
+
+1. **ABS config/db lost:** restore from the last ABS backup (config + metadata
+   volumes on the Pi5 HDD). OIDC server settings are persisted in the DB; if
+   the backup predates OIDC enablement, re-apply
+   `apply-abs-settings.sh`.
+2. **Keycloak client lost:** re-run `setup-keycloak.sh` to recreate groups,
+   client, roles, mappers, and re-seed `michael`; re-apply ABS settings with
+   the new secret.
+3. **Keycloak down:** the local `admin` break-glass account still logs in
+   (local auth, no Keycloak dependency). Use it to operate ABS until Keycloak
+   is restored.
+4. **Secret compromise:** rotate immediately (§3) and restart ABS.
+
+## 5. Break-glass procedure
+
+- **Purpose:** emergency local administration when Keycloak or SSO is
+  unavailable. Not for daily use.
+- **Account:** local `admin` (confidential client / SSO untouched).
+- **Setup / rotation:** `pi/audiobookshelf/scripts/break-glass-setup.sh`
+  generates a ≥192-bit password, sets it on the local `admin`, and delivers it
+  **exactly once** via the operator Telegram channel (password body only).
+- **Verification (no password in evidence):** `verify-break-glass.sh` reads the
+  password interactively (no echo) and prints only PASS/FAIL + redacted
+  metadata.
+- **Operator duty:** store the received password **offline**; rotate on a
+  schedule and after any suspected exposure. Never commit or log it.
